### HYMN CXIII

#### A charm to banish the fiend Grāhi

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0611301">1</span></span>This sin the
Gods wiped off and laid on Trita, and Trita wiped  
   it off on human beings.  
  Thence if the female fiend hath made thee captive, the Gods by  
   prayer shall banish her and free thee.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0611302">2</span></span>Enter the
particles of light and vapours, go to the rising fogs or  
   mists, O Evil!  
  Hence! vanish in the foams of rivers. Pūshan, wipe woes away  
   upon the babe-destroyer!  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0611303">3</span></span>Stored in
twelve separate places lies what Trita hath wiped away,  
   the sins of human beings.  
  Thence if the female fiend hath made thee captive, the Gods by  
   prayer shall banish her and free thee.

